The subject property is a 2 bedroom, 1 bathroom, 800 square foot ranch. The subject property is 52 years old, built in 1965 and is situated on a 0.46 acre lot.  The subject property is in fair to poor condition and quality of construction is average.  The subject property is not a part of an HOA. The subject is located in a lake community with homes of similar size and style. Roads are paved and easily navigable. Subject is close to all amenities. Market conditions are stable.  Employment conditions are stable. The neighborhood values range from $19,900 to $749,900 with an average marketing time of 76 days. Financing is not available for the property, the roof has failed, the interior is unfinished, the foundation is crumbling.  The area is 70% owner occupied.  There are currently 72 comparable listings in the area, 3 of which are REO. Comps are sitting on the market and then being taken off because they are not selling for the list price. The target buyer for the subject property is an investor. 
The subject property appears to have been gutted and the former owners were in the process of renovations. However, they are left undone and the house is in a poor state. The exterior concrete foundation is literally crumbling and the front concrete steps have holes in them and are crumbling as well. The roof is covered in moss and has leaked in some areas and needs to be completely torn off and replaced. The exterior trim needs to be painted. The plumbing has freeze damage and there are many areas that need repair. The furnace and well/septic need inspections and likely many repars themselves. After all that is said and done the entire inside of the home needs to be finished. Many rooms are stripped to the subfloor. The entire asset needs flooring or for the existing hardwood to be refinished. The entire asset needs for the drywall to be completed, mudded and painted. The kitchen has nothing of use in it and needs to be completely done, including appliances. The bathroom needs to be updated as well. Repairs are not recommended as there is little opportunity for return on investment and a likelihood of further necessary repairs being discovered. 
The below comps were determined to be the best indicators of value for the subject property:
313 Midway Dr, Highland Lakes NJ
This sold comp was identified on the agent BPO.  This comp is a 2 bedroom, 1 bathroom, 1002 square foot ranch on .22 acre lot.  This comp is in good condition but does need some repairs and updates.  This comp is 48 years old, built in 1969 and is located 6 blocks from the subject property.  This comp sold fair market for $85,000 in October 2017 after 169 days on the market.  https://www.zillow.com/homedetails/313-Midway-Dr-Highland-Lakes-NJ-07422/39960985_zpid/

56 Breakneck Rd, Highland Lakes NJ
This sold comp was identified on the supplemental BPO.  This comp is a 2 bedroom, 1 bathroom, 768 square foot ranch on .21 acres.  This comp is has no updates.  This comp is 43 years old, built in 1974 and is located 1.71 miles from the subject property.  This comp sold fair market for $53,594 in July 2017 after 202 days on the market.  
https://www.zillow.com/homedetails/56-Breakneck-Rd-Highland-Lakes-NJ-07422/39961747_zpid/

156 Coon Den Rd, Highland Lakes NJ
This listed comp was identified on both the agent and supplemental BPO.  This comp is a 3 bedroom, 1 bathroom, 800 square foot ranch on .16 acres.  This comp is very dated but has been maintained.  This comp is 49 years old, built in 1968 and is located 3 blocks from the subject property.  This comp is listed as fair market for $109,900 (reduced from $137,500) and has been on the market for 270 days. https://www.trulia.com/homes/New_Jersey/Highland_Lakes/sold/709079-156-Coon-Den-Rd-Highland-Lakes-NJ-07422
